        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 18 at 4:18PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 418 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of De Queen, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
De Queen, Gillham, West Line, West Otis and Geneva.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
